To the left is DURING my bodybuilding season of this year, super lean, tons of cardio, strict diet; tracking macros >> not sustainable.

To the right is today; no strict diet, intuitively eating before vacay. BUT this is what I look like coming back from an epic 8 day / 7 night Mexico cruise 🇲🇽🚢 I enjoyed ALL the FOOD I wanted, I had a few drinks & lived in the moment as y’all saw on my stories 😋 (worked out M-F; rested Sat/Sun)

I missed out on so much over the years because I was prepping for bodybuilding shows & I’ve accomplished so much; so thankful for all that I’ve learned & proud of the woman I’ve become because of it over the last 3 years. 

But, I was anxious at social events & my mind was consumed with thoughts about food & my body. I found it hard to enjoy any special moment when my thought process was always elsewhere.

Now there will be a time & place for people to be tracking, especially if you do have strict body composition goals...do what works for you. I just wanted to share that my healthiest & happiest self has been when I have focused on
food freedom rather than restriction ✨

I go out and enjoy myself. It's not to say these thoughts don't still creep up, it’s been 7 weeks since I decided to pause on my bodybuilding career. In those weeks I just have learned to push them aside & focus on what truly matters to me. 

Life is short. If you are young, don't waste precious moments. If you are older, don't let anymore time pass by when you aren't living your life to the fullest.
